    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (75.90) headlines our offensive production, buoyed by a favorable matchup against Martinez (xERA 4.59). With a high base projection and a significant boost from his placement in the #3 spot, he is our primary anchor. We are also leaning heavily into the top-tier efficiency of **Bryson Stott** (71.93), who benefits from an elite platoon edge against Mahle, and **Gleyber Torres** (67.52), whose projection is propped up significantly by a favorable matchup against the lefty P\u00e9rez. Both **Jonathan Aranda** and **Will Smith** deserve mention as strong plays, each exceeding the 64-point threshold by leveraging solid batting order support and positive SP skill matchups. \n\nThe most difficult personnel decision centered on our bench, where **Matt Chapman** (44.35) narrowly missed the final cut. While his underlying metrics against Luzardo are respectable, the optimizer penalized his projected output due to the opponent's elite ability to control the running game\u2014a critical factor given our aggressive pursuit of the scarce SB category. **Luis Arraez** and **Jung Hoo Lee** followed closely, but their projected efficiencies failed to clear the threshold set by the lower-order volatility of **Jeremiah Jackson** and **Gavin Sheets**, who retain upside due to park-factor inflation.\n\nWe must remain vigilant regarding the risk associated with **Tyler Freeman** (44.80). Facing Burns, who enters with a daunting 2.76 xERA, **Tyler Freeman** is teetering on the edge of our viability floor; he is a marginal start that we are only deploying for lack of superior alternatives. We are satisfied with the rest of the lineup, particularly **Yainer Diaz** and **Taylor Ward**, who should see a measurable boost from park effects. Keep a close eye on any late weather shifts, as these could easily swing the marginal starts of **Masyn Winn**, **Tyler Freeman**, and **Gavin Sheets** into sub-40 \"Below Floor\" territory.",
